wikipedia_page.main: Stanley John Webb (born 6 December 1947) is a former English footballer who scored 40 goals from 167 appearances in the Football League playing for Middlesbrough, Carlisle United, Brentford and Darlington in the 1970s. A forward, he also played non-league football for clubs including Whitby Town and Guisborough Town, for whom he scored the club's first FA Cup goal, in the 1978–79 first qualifying round against Consett.Webb attended Middlesbrough High School, and captained their under-15 basketball team to the English Schools championship in 1963.
